f=AI & Agents/gauge/custom/llm-ops-basics/SKILL.md · in=Operational discipline running LLM-backed agents production: golden-set evals, drift detection, version pinning. Catalog marked marketplace; strong candidate (hamelsmu/evals-skills) exists adopting multi-file skill unreviewed violates our intake rules built custom now, candidate queued scout. · p=Model behavior changes under your feet: provider updates, prompt edits, tool changes. Without pinned versions stable golden set, degradation discovered users instead gauge. · wu=Setting running recurring golden-set eval., model/provider/prompt version changes anywhere fleet., Scorecard flags need behavioral (not operational) confirmation. · st:/ Protocol=PIN (record model+version+config agent) GOLDEN SET (operator-supplied task set, versioned) RUN (same set, cadence) COMPARE (vs last run pinned baseline) ALERT (drift degradation-routing). · in=Version pinning: agent's model, version/date, generation config recorded fleet registry entry (meta) "latest" version. Provider-forced changes recorded unplanned version events trigger off-cadence golden run. Golden set: `<FILL_IN: operator golden task set representative tasks agent expected-behavior rubrics>`. Never invented gauge (rule 0.5); until exists, skill runs method-only says so. Cadence: `<FILL_IN: suggested weekly, aligned scorecard>`. Blind scoring rubrics allow (forge's benchmarking-discipline shares method). Drift verdicts: PASS BEHAVIOR DRIFT (score drop beyond rubric tolerance) FORMAT DRIFT (shape changed). drifts route forge degradation-routing run artifacts attached. Never tune-to-the-test: golden set changes Rail proposals (they redefine "good"), set fleet adapted gets refreshed, relaxed. · of=Dated golden-run report: per-agent scores baseline, verdicts, version stamps. Append-only alongside scorecards. · pr=Pin everything; unpinned fleet can't distinguish regressions provider's., golden set definition "still works" treat edits seriously charter edits., Evals evidence routing, never verdict themselves (same rule quinn's eval-harness). · f=golden set (the normal state until operator supplies one): pin versions anyway, log version events, use scorecard operational metrics drift signal clearly flagged behavioral-blind-spot. · b:with Other Skills=agent-quality-scorecard: operational metrics; skill: behavioral metrics. feed degradation-routing., forge's benchmarking-discipline: compares CANDIDATE models golden set; skill watches INCUMBENT., quinn's eval-harness: pre-release gate; this: post-release watch.